\par }{\b The Guildhall Ward
\par 
\par }{\'93Well you\rquote ve paid your jink, and show you the Guildhall Ward I shall. The name itself says as much as most cutters can, and in many ways it\rquote s not too different from me home, the Market Ward. But power I tell you, it\rquote 
s creeping into the ward from the gutters on up.
\par 
\par \'93Eh? Me? Well I\rquote ve got my own opinions on the ward certainly. The way I see it, things\rquote 
ll be coming full circle eventually, and influence is fleeing the factions like cranium rats in an astral storm and piling up high with the guilds. Of course, I\rquote m the head of one of them, so me views a bit slanted you might say.
\par 
\par \'93But a good bunch of people the ward has, and I like to think I know most of them. So don\rquote t be surprised if I happen to nod and wave to half of them as we start this little walk.\'94 \endash  Kylie the Tout
\par 
\par The Guildhall Ward, in its storied past was once, in the years before the Great Upheaval, the center of real power in Sigil. Then, before the Lady reduced the number of factions to fiftenn from the hundreds of squabbling, competing ones before, the real
 powers in Sigil were the talented groupings of workers and craftsmen of the Guildhall Ward. By pooling their numbers and power, they could out maneuver the ever-fighting factions. But the consolidation of the factions after the Great Upheaval saw to the 
decline and eventual end to the guilds grip on Sigil, and indeed many of them ceased to exist in time as the factions took control of more and more of the Cage\rquote s institutions.
\par 
\par Since the fall of the factions as organized or official powers within Sigil, it 
would appear that the guilds have been making a resurgence in importance and visibility. Most of the guild houses lay in a rough circle around the center of the ward, clustered near to the Great Gymnasium. Among other examples, both the Escort and Touts G
uild and the Builders Fellowship lie at opposite ends of Turtle Lane. Downwards some five blocks from the Gymnasium stands the Council of Innkeepers on Shallowglass Lane, while the Order of Master Clerks and Scribes sits nestled at the end of Dancer
\rquote s Court.
\par }{\b\i 
\par Gymnasium District}{
